===Etymology===
From Arabic[[Category:Arabic derivations]] [[ﺮﺏﻥﺀ]] (khanbar) (the 'kh' representing a fricative aspirant), ambergris.  Ambergris, of animal origin, somehow became confused with the fossil resin, of vegetable origin, so the French[[Category:French derivations]] language differentiated them as ''ambre gris'', grey amber, and ''ambre jaune'', yellow amber.  English adopted this differentiation in the respective forms ambergris and amber.<!--Interesting, but not relevant to the English etymology: The German[[Category:German derivations]] language adopted respectively, ''Amber'' (or ''Ambra'')  and ''Bernstein''.-->

===Noun===
'''amber'''  (''[[uncountable]]'')
